{"_id":"e343bc00c7de151a","name":"Eye Light Systems (Alphaware)","type":"cyberware","img":"icons/equipment/head/helm-visor-technological.webp","system":{"grade":{"label":"Alphaware","mult":0.8,"costMult":2},"essence_cost":0.16,"installed":false,"category":"bodyware","cost":2400,"availability":"","street_index":1.5,"mods":{},"description":"Eye lights, another nifty new piece of work, can be either a tool or a weapon. The plain-vanilla light system mounts high-powered, low-heat lights in the cybereye that channel a tight, polarized beam outward down a path parallel to the optical center of the eye. An amount of light sufficient to see with standard low-light eyes falls wherever the user is looking. The tight beam and polarization minimize scatter from the eye, so the light can't be seen unless someone's staring right at you."},"folder":null,"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"shadowrun2e"}}
